Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish. Lay chicken breasts in the bottom of the pan and place a piece of Swiss cheese on each breast. In a small bowl or measuring cup combine soup with sherry. Pour over chicken. Combine stuffing and melted butter; spread over chicken. Bake, covered, in preheated oven for 60 minutes. Uncover and bake for another 60 minutes.